---
import { SoarOrbital } from './SoarOrbital';
---

<section id="what-is-soar" class="relative py-20 md:py-28">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-6">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-14 items-center">
      <!-- Left: Punchy explainer -->
      <div>
        <span class="text-heading bg-heading/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-medium text-xs">Why OpenSOAR</span>
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-heading mt-4 mb-4">
          Automation platforms got<br/>the abstraction wrong
        </h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-text leading-relaxed mb-6">
          SOAR tools, runbook builders, no-code automators &mdash; they all invent their own way to define workflows. Visual canvases you can't diff. YAML you can't debug. Proprietary SDKs that lock you in. Per-action pricing that punishes you for automating more.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text leading-relaxed">
          <strong class="text-heading" style="font-family: 'Inter Tight', sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Open</span><span style="font-weight: 700;">SOAR</span></strong> uses the abstraction that already exists: Python. Your playbooks are async functions with decorators. Test them, version them, review them in PRs. Apache 2.0, self-hosted, free.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Orbital visualization — alert sources flowing into SOAR engine -->
      <div class="hidden lg:flex items-center justify-center">
        <SoarOrbital client:visible />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
